INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4450','letter','1781-04-08','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Benjamin','Tallmadge','','individual','','The success of the proposed enterprise, must depend on the absence of the British fleet, the secrecy of the attempt, and a knowledge of the exact situation of the enemy.','ltr_gwa4450.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4451','letter','1781-04-09','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','John','Laurens','','individual','','several interesting events have happened ; some favorable, others adverse. Among the former may be reckoned Morgan\'s brilliant action with Tarleton ; among the latter, the advantages gained by Lord Cornwallis over General Greene.','ltr_gwa4451.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4452','letter','1781-04-10','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','We are greatly indebted to the Chevalier Destouches for the disposition he shows to undertake the expedition to Penobscot, and to you for your readiness to furnish a detachment of troops','ltr_gwa4452.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4453','letter','1781-04-11','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','While I give you credit for the manoeuvre by which you removed the British ships from before Annapolis, I am sorry, as matters are circumstanced, that you have put yourself so much further from the point','ltr_gwa4453.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4454','letter','1781-04-14','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','The contingencies appeared to me so remote, in the conversations I had with Count De Rochambeau, that I could not justify myself in withdrawing a detachment already so far advanced','ltr_gwa4454.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4455','letter','1781-04-16','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Johnathan','Trumball','','individual','','Colonel Harrison, who has acted as my secretary since the beginning of 1776, has accepted an honorable and profitable civil appointment in the State of Maryland, and is gone to enjoy it.','ltr_gwa4455.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4456','letter','1781-04-18','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Nathanael','Greene','','individual','','Your private letter of the 18th ultimo came safe to hand. Although the honors of the field did not fall to your lot, I am convinced you deserved them.','ltr_gwa4456.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4457','letter','1781-04-21','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','Though the situation of southern affairs would not permit me to recall your corps to this army, yet it was with great reluctance I could resolve upon seeing you separated from head-quarters.','ltr_gwa4457.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4458','letter','1781-04-22','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','I have received your several letters, and am extremely concerned at the temper of your detachment, and the desertions that are taking place.','ltr_gwa4458.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4459','letter','1781-04-25','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','George','Clark','','individual','','At the request of Governor Jefferson, I have already given orders to the commandant at Fort Pitt to afford you every assistance in his power, in the prosecution of your intended expedition.','ltr_gwa4459.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4460','letter','1781-04-27','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Alexander','Hamilton','','individual','','The officers of the line contend, without having reference to particular persons, that it is a hardship and reflection upon them to introduce brevet officers into commands, of some permanence','ltr_gwa4460.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4461','letter','1781-04-30','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','I assure your Excellency, that I feel extreme pain at the occasion of that part of your letter of the 26th instant, which relates to an intercepted letter of mine published by the enemy.','ltr_gwa4461.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4462','letter','1781-04-30','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Benjamin','Tallmadge','','individual','','Besides these, you are also sensible there are many things upon a smaller scale, which are necessary to be reported, and that whatever intelligence is communicated ought to be, not in general terms, but in detail, and with the greatest precision.','ltr_gwa4462.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4463','letter','1781-04-30','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Lund','Washington','','individual','','I am very sorry to hear of your loss. I am a little sorry to hear of my own ; but that which gives me most concern is, that you should go on board the enemy\'s vessels, and furnish them with refreshments.','ltr_gwa4463.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4464','letter','1781-05-04','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','A false idea, arising from the consideration of his being my steward, and in that character more the trustee and guardian of my property than the representative of my honor, has misled his judgment and plunged him into error','ltr_gwa4464.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4465','letter','1781-05-05','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','and am extremely rejoiced to learn, that the spirit of discontent had so entirely subsided, and that the parade of desertion would probably be totally stopped among the troops under your command.','ltr_gwa4465.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4466','letter','1781-05-10','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Meshech','Weare','','individual','','From the post of Saratoga to that of Dobbs\'s Ferry inclusive, I believe there is not (by the returns and reports I have received) at this moment one day\'s supply of meat for the army on hand.','ltr_gwa4466.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4467','letter','1781-05-11','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','John','Sullivan','','individual','','This, and a recent instance in the Pennsylvania regiment of artillery in proof of the absolute necessity of adopting some mode, by which the whole army may be bound, and a stop thereby be put to those disputes, which keep it in a continual state of distraction and discontent','ltr_gwa4467.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4468','letter','1781-05-11','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Benjamin','Lincoln','','individual','','so great are my apprehensions, on the score of provisions, that I am sending General Heath purposely to the eastern States to represent our distresses, and to endeavour to fix a plan for our regular supply in future.','ltr_gwa4468.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4469','letter','1781-05-14','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','','De Barras','','individual','','Give me leave to congratulate you on your safe arrival, and your appointment to the command of his Most Christian Majesty\'s fleet and sea forces upon these coasts.','ltr_gwa4469.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4471','letter','1781-05-15','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Paul','Jones','','individual','','My partial acquaintance with either our naval or commercial affairs makes it altogether impossible for me to account for the unfortunate delay of those articles of military stores and clothing','ltr_gwa4471.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4472','letter','1781-05-15','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Ezra','Styles','','individual','','For the honor conferred on me by the President and Fellows of the University of Yale College, by the degree of Doctor of Laws, my warmest thanks are offered','ltr_gwa4472.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4473','letter','1781-05-17','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Alexander','Scammell','','individual','','I have received intelligence, that a party of the enemy are establishing themselves at or near Fort Lee, and building a blockhouse, or some kind of work.','ltr_gwa4473.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4474','letter','1781-05-23','Weathersfield','NY','US','George','Washington','','Chevalier','De La Luzerne','','individual','','The letter, which I have the honor to enclose from the Count De Rochambeau, will, I imagine, inform you of the intended march of the French army towards the North River, and of the destination of the King\'s squadron now in the harbour of Newport','ltr_gwa4474.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4475','letter','1781-05-24','Weathersfield','NY','US','George','Washington','','Meshech','Weare','','individual','','In consequence of a conference held between the Count De Rochambeau and myself at this place, the French army will march, as soon as circumstances will admit, and form a junction with the American army upon the North River.','ltr_gwa4475.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4476','letter','1781-05-28','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Louis','Duportail','','individual','','I have only to request, therefore, that you will be pleased to make the estimates of the articles in your department necessary for the operation','ltr_gwa4476.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4477','letter','1781-05-28','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Elias','Dayton','','individual','','The late accounts from New York are mysterious and perplexing, but they at any rate demand that we should be in readiness to move.','ltr_gwa4477.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4478','letter','1781-05-29','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','John','Sullivan','','individual','','No arguments were necessary to convince me of the very great public utility, which would result from the success of the plan you proposed laying before Congress.','ltr_gwa4478.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4479','letter','1781-05-31','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','Your conduct upon every occasion meets my approbation, but in none more than in your refusing to hold a correspondence with Arnold.','ltr_gwa4479.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4480','letter','1781-06-01','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Nathanael','Greene','','individual','','The difficulties, which you daily encounter and surmount with your small force, add not a little to your reputation','ltr_gwa4480.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4481','letter','1781-06-04','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','I had last evening the honor of receiving your favor of the 31st of May by the Duke De Lauzun, who informs me, that he is authorized by your Excellency and Count de Barras to enter into a free communication with me upon the subject of the council of war ','ltr_gwa4481.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4482','letter','1781-06-04','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','I felt a most sensible pleasure when I heard of your acceptance of the late appointment of Congress to regulate the finances of this country.','ltr_gwa4482.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4483','letter','1781-06-05','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','James','Clinton','','individual','','The six companies of Van Schaick\'s regiment have since sailed. Hazen\'s will follow to-morrow.','ltr_gwa4483.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4484','letter','1781-06-07','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','John','Mathews','','individual','','I am very sorry for the disagreeable situation of our suffering soldiery at Charleston, and wish they could be relieved without adding to the pressure under which we at present given.','ltr_gwa4484.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4485','letter','1781-06-08','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Thomas','Jefferson','','individual','','The progress, which the enemy are making in Virginia, is very alarming, not only to the State immediately invaded, but to all the rest','ltr_gwa4485.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4486','letter','1781-06-13','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','I flatter myself, that the whole convoy will arrive in safety in some of the eastern ports, as I believe the British ships are all cruising off the Hook.','ltr_gwa4486.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4487','letter','1781-06-13','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Chevalier','De La Luzerne','','individual','','Having been made acquainted by the Count De Rochambeau, with the design of the Count de Grasse to come to this coast with his fleet, I cannot forbear expressing my ardent wishes, that a body of land forces might also attend this naval armament','ltr_gwa4487.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4488','letter','1781-06-21','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','George','Clinton','','individual','','I have just received a letter from Brigadier-General Clinton, enclosing the examination of two prisoners who were taken lately by one of his scouts ; from whence it appears the enemy in Canada have not made any movements in force','ltr_gwa4488.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4489','letter','1781-06-23','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','William','Irvine','','individual','','I can easily conceive the disappointment and mortification you have suffered, upon finding the flattering prospects of filling your line so unexpectedly blasted','ltr_gwa4489.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4490','letter','1781-06-24','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','I have the pleasure to observe the progress you make in the march of the troops under your command, and your intentions to come to my camp in person from Hartford.','ltr_gwa4490.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4491','letter','1781-06-25','New Windsor','NY','US','George','Washington','','John','Stark','','individual','','Upon finding it necessary, for the operations of the campaign, to recall the Continental troops from the northward, I have ordered six hundred militia from the counties of Berkshire and Hampshire to that quarter','ltr_gwa4491.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4492','letter','1781-06-27','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','It would have given me the greatest pleasure could I have made it convenient to meet you at Newtown ; but independently of many arrangements, which are necessary at the first taking of the field, I am detained','ltr_gwa4492.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4493','letter','1781-06-28','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','Your opinion of the absolute necessity of a repeal of all Under laws, before a new species of paper, though upon ever so good an establishment, will gain credit with the public, is certainly founded upon reason','ltr_gwa4493.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4494','letter','1781-06-29','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','I have since that heard a thousand vague reports of your situation, and that of the enemy, but none of them satisfactory.','ltr_gwa4494.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4495','letter','1781-06-30','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','David','Cobb','','individual','','Its object is to inform the Count, that I have in contemplation a very sudden surprise of some post of the enemy, which will be of very great importance in our operations','ltr_gwa4495.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4496','letter','1781-06-30','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','','Waterbury','','individual','','You will immediately on the receipt of this be pleased to collect as many men of your command as you possibly can, and march them from the place of rendezvous, so as to form a junction, without fail, with Colonel Sheldon','ltr_gwa4496.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4497','letter','1781-06-30','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','George','Clinton','','individual','','In the fullest confidence I inform you, that I intend to make an attempt by surprise upon the enemy\'s posts on the north end of York Island, on Monday night.','ltr_gwa4497.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4498','letter','1781-07-01','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','Benjamin','Lincoln','','individual','','My ideas, as to the most probable mode of attaining this object, have been minutely detailed in the several conversations which we have had upon the subject, and you have been furnished with such papers as I have been able to collect','ltr_gwa4498.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4499','letter','1781-07-01','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','','Waterbury','','individual','','As the Duke will be a stranger to that part of the country, which is to be the scene of your operations, it will be in your power to give him much assistance and information','ltr_gwa4499.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4500','letter','1781-07-02','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','I think it will be very well for your Excellency to proceed to-morrow to North Castle, where you will continue until you assemble your whole force','ltr_gwa4500.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4501','letter','1781-07-02','Peekskill','NY','US','George','Washington','','Henry','Knox','','individual','','The arrangement you have made, for the periods of transportation of the heavy stores from Philadelphia, agrees perfectly with my ideas of the matter','ltr_gwa4501.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4502','letter','1781-07-03','Valentines Hill','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','The operations of this day are over, and I am sorry to say, that I have not had the happiness to succeed to my wishes, although I think very essential benefit will result to our future operations from the opportunity','ltr_gwa4502.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4503','letter','1781-07-04','White Plains','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','I am much inclined to wish you to give them one more day\'s rest in your present quarters, and the more so, as there is now no real occasion for making an uncommon degree of haste.','ltr_gwa4503.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4504','letter','1781-07-15','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','I sincerely congratulate you on the favorable turn of affairs announced in your last, and I hope you will be enabled to maintain that superiority, which you seem to be gaining over Lord Cornwallis.','ltr_gwa4504.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4505','letter','1781-07-13','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','I beg you to be assured, that I never can think your correspondence tedious or troublesome. Duty as well as inclination will always prompt me to listen with pleasure to your observations upon the state of our public affairs','ltr_gwa4505.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4506','letter','1781-07-11','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','William','Alexander','','individual','','While I am with the detachment of the army below, you will remain in command here. Your principal attention will be paid to the good order of the camp, and the security of the baggage and stores left in it.','ltr_gwa4506.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4507','letter','1781-07-15','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Richard','Lee','','individual','','The distresses of Virginia I am but too well acquainted with ; but the plan you have suggested as a relief for it is, in my judgment, a greater proof of your unbounded confidence in me','ltr_gwa4507.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4508','letter','1781-07-21','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','','De Barras','','individual','','I have no doubt but the reasons which induce you to decline the removal of the squadron under your command to the Chesapeake at this time are founded in propriety','ltr_gwa4508.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4509','letter','1781-07-25','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Samuel','Huntington','','individual','','I have been honored with your favor of the 10th, announcing your resignation of the chair of Congress and the election of Mr. McKean to that important station.','ltr_gwa4509.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4510','letter','1781-07-30','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Nathanael','Greene','','individual','','By our movements in this quarter, and the main army taking a position near New York, and making every preparation for a serious attempt upon that place, we have already produced a happy effect','ltr_gwa4510.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4511','letter','1781-07-30','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','I am convinced, that your desire to be with this army arises principally from a wish to be actively useful. You will not, therefore, regret your stay in Virginia until matters are reduced to a greater degree of certainty','ltr_gwa4511.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4512','letter','1781-08-02','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','It seems reduced almost to a certainty, that the enemy will reinforce New York with part of their troops from Virginia. In that case, the attempt against the former must be laid aside','ltr_gwa4512.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4513','letter','1781-08-02','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Meshech','Weare','','individual','','I regret being obliged to inform your Excellency, that I find myself at this late period very little stronger than I was when the army first moved out of their quarters.','ltr_gwa4513.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4514','letter','1781-08-15','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','I cannot learn that any troops have yet arrived at New York from Virginia. A fleet of twenty sail came in last Saturday with troops, but they are said to be Hessian recruits from Europe.','ltr_gwa4514.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4515','letter','1781-08-16','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','As the remaining part of Colonel Cortlandt\'s regiment is now ordered to join the main army, I have given directions to General Clinton to leave with you a small guard of men','ltr_gwa4515.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4516','letter','1781-08-17','Phillipsburg','NY','US','George','Washington','','Alexandre','De Grasse','','individual','','In consequence of the despatches received from your Excellency by the frigate Concorde, it has been judged expedient to give up for the present the enterprise against New York, and turn our attention towards the south','ltr_gwa4516.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4517','letter','1781-08-17','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','Besides the provision necessary at the Head of Elk to carry the troops down the bay, a very considerable quantity will be wanted in Virginia.','ltr_gwa4517.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4518','letter','1781-08-19','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','William','Heath','','individual','','The security of West Point and the posts in the Highlands is to be considered the first object of your attention. In order to effect this, you will make such dispositions as in your judgement the circumstances shall from time to time require','ltr_gwa4518.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4519','letter','1781-08-21','Kings Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Jean Baptiste','De Vimeur','','individual','','I am very sorry for the difficulties and impediments, which fall in the way of your march, and hope they will decrease as you proceed.','ltr_gwa4519.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gwa4520','letter','1781-08-21','Kings Ferry','NY','US','George','Washington','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','the troops destined for the southern quarter are now in motion. The American detachment is already on the west side of the Hudson.','ltr_gwa4520.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of George Washington Being His Correspondence, Addresses, Messages, and Other Papers, Official and Private, Selected and Published from the Original Manuscripts. Vol VIII, Jared Sparks, 1839');
